  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tortillas</strong> to a baking tray&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until they're golden and crispy - these are your <strong>crispy tortillas</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>into wedges, then separate the<strong> red onion wedges</strong> into 'petals'</p>\r\n<p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> tomato wedges</strong>&nbsp;to a&nbsp;separate baking tray with the <strong>feta</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle the<strong> tomato wedges</strong> and<strong> feta</strong> with the&nbsp;<strong>dried oregano</strong> and drizzle them both with<strong> olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until the<strong> tomato wedges</strong>&nbsp;and the<strong> feta</strong>&nbsp;are hot to touch</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>red onion petals&nbsp;</strong>with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and a small splash of<strong>&nbsp;water</strong>, cover with a lid and cook for 3-4 min or until they're beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/967.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
